MocoNews.net: mobile content news: &ldquo;Mobile Blogging generates an immediate reduction of up to 70% in the propensity of a user to churn.&rdquo;
Results of a 12-month survey of two million subscribers on four operators which were using NewBay&rsquo;s Software FoneBlog mobile blogging and multimedia album solution have been released.
According to NewBay the result comes from increased loyalty – based on personal content on the moblog. What is obvious here is if you have personal content and you can&rsquo;t move/download it simply, then there is a barrier to change.
